params.tokenAddress: Address of the token in the pair
params.tokenAmount: Amount of tokens to add as liquidity

constructor.details: Constructor sets the owner and price feed address

params._priceFeed: Address of the price feed oracle

createPair(address,uint256).details: Creates a new token pair for trading

params.initialTokenAmount: Initial amount of tokens for liquidity
params.tokenAddress: Address of the token to be paired with ETH

params.tokenAddress: Address of the token to swap

returns._0: The amount of ETH that would be received

getExchangeRate(address).details: Gets the current exchange rate for a token pair

params.tokenAddress: Address of the token in the pair

returns._0: The current exchange rate (tokens per ETH)

getLiquidity(address).details: Gets the current liquidity for a token pair

params.tokenAddress: Address of the token in the pair

getTokensOutForETH(address,uint256).details: Gets the amount of tokens that would be received for a given ETH amount

params.tokenAddress: Address of the token to receive

returns._0: The amount of tokens that would be received

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeLiquidity(address,uint256).details: Removes liquidity from a token pair

params.tokenAddress: Address of the token in the pair

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner.
